HEADWORD: Comedo
<hw>Com"e*do</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Comedones</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L., a glutton. See
<er>Comestible</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A small nodule or
cystic tumor, common on the nose, etc., which on pressure allows the
escape of a yellow wormlike mass of retained oily secretion, with a
black head (dirt).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Comedown</ent>⟦br⟧
